      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions used for validation must be documented and traceable to the COU operating envelope at Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "The FDA benchmark experimental conditions (flow rates 2.5–7.5 L/min, rotational speeds 2000–3500 RPM, bovine blood at 37°C) are documented in the published FDA study and are within the CPB operating envelope. Test condition documentation meets Gradation 2 requirements."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metrics between model predictions and experimental data must be reported with uncertainty bounds at Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "CFD-predicted NIH values were compared against experimental measurements across all 5 operating points. Mean absolute percentage error was 12.3% with experimental uncertainty of ±15%. Comparison metrics including RMSE and R² are reported. Gradation 2 requirements met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The QoIs used in validation (NIH, MIH, RH) must be directly relevant to the clinical hemolysis decision at Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index (RH) is the primary acceptance criterion for the COU decision. NIH and MIH are the standard regulatory QoIs for hemolysis assessment per FDA guidance. These QoIs are directly relevant to the worst-case identification objective. Gradation 2 satisfied."
    },
    {
